title: Kaloko-Honokōhau National Historical Park: Nature
body: Explore This Park    Learn About the Park     Nature             Nature        In winter hump-back whales occasionally frequent the park's waters. Tom Fake photo      Watch the waves crash upon the sandy shores.  Catch a glimpse of a sea turtle surfacing for a breath as a native shore bird takes flight towards the horizon.  The beauty of nature will surround and inspire you at Kaloko-Honokohau National Historical Park.
